The number of people who supported Jacob Zuma at his first state capture appearance has dwindled to just a few dozen. Govan Whittles reports live from Braamfontein. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The number of people who supported former president, Jacob Zuma at the state capture inquiry has dwindled to just a few dozen. The leadership of MKVMA says it didn't have enough time to organise more support. WATCH: Zondo makes statement before recusal application Zuma is back at the state capture inquiry after being subpoenaed last month. 